<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1032153-if-you-think-is-the-best-book-ever-can">If you think is the best book ever, can anyone recommend other similar books/stories? No horror or ghosts needed - just that perfect psychological thriller. Anyone??? Please???</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1032153'><a id="like_count_community_question_1032153" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1032153?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">26 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F89724.We_Have_Always_Lived_in_the_Castle">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1032153-if-you-think-is-the-best-book-ever-can">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1032153-if-you-think-is-the-best-book-ever-can">See all 37 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/35207026-jess"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1593028839i/35207026._UY100_CR14,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/35207026-jess">Jess</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Pick up Flannery O&apos;Connor if you haven&apos;t already. Highly recommend her collections, specifically &quot;Everything that Rises Must Converge&quot; and &quot;A Good Man<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Pick up Flannery O'Connor if you haven't already. Highly recommend her collections, specifically "Everything that Rises Must Converge" and "A Good Man is Hard to Find." (Take a look at the title short story "A Good Man is Hard to Find" or "Good Country People.") Poe is another obvious one, though more horror/ gothic. Henry James' "The Turn of the Screw" is another good one for you. Other short stories: Joyce Carol Oates' "Where Are You Going, Where Have You Been?" and Charlotte Perkins Gilman's "The Yellow Wallpaper." This is probably the MOST obnoxiously obvious, but have you read "The Lottery" ? :)<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

