<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/2203681-graciekat"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1548635731i/2203681._UX100_CR0,19,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/2203681-graciekat">GracieKat</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
     &lt;spoiler&gt;I assumed it was Merricat since one of her favorite things she lists early on is the poisonous mushroom. The big mystery for me is why, exac<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
     &lt;spoiler&gt;I assumed it was Merricat since one of her favorite things she lists early on is the poisonous mushroom. The big mystery for me is why, exactly, did she poison them. For some reason I always thought it was because she wanted Constance all to herself since Constance was the only one who never used sugar on berries. She also pictures people dying, dead or in agony often and it pleases her. <br /><br />This was something I caught later but Uncle Julian says that their mother and father were arguing about something the father wanted to do but the mother wouldn't hear of it. Perhaps they were arguing about putting Merricat into an asylum or institution. &lt;/spoiler&gt;<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
